review_blob: This is one of the better ambers Ive had the pleasure of tasting. It did not have the typical bitterness of an amber but more of a sweet taste to it. Great for BBQs.
Big fan of this classic. Great sweet, malty taste and aroma to this brew. It has a soft fnish and doesnt leave any bitter aftertaste.
By far the best of the summer beers. Crisp and refreshing. Goes great with seafood dishes.
A good summer beer when there is no corona about. A little too light for me to drink regularly.
